James de Villiers and Nation Nyoka, News24Paramedics tend to a wounded man after the attempted hijacking of a police car in Alberton. (Supplied) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - &nbsp;A man was shot in the head when he allegedly tried to hijack a police vehicle in Alberton on Monday afternoon. He was shot while trying to drive away with the car on the N3, police sources told News24.&nbsp;ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said the car veered off the road during a shootout between police and the would-be hijacker.&nbsp;The police officer who was in the car sustained minor injuries. The man was taken to a nearby hospital. A second person was arrested.&nbsp;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.